2005-10-27 12:51  pgregory

	* configure.ac, render/version.h: Update ready for release 1.0.1

2005-10-27 12:40  pgregory

	* aqsis/aqsis.cpp, display/display.cpp, librib2/parser.yxx,
	  libshaderexecenv/shadeops.cpp, libslparse/funcdef.cpp,
	  libslparse/typecheck.cpp, render/curves.cpp, render/lights.cpp,
	  render/options.cpp, render/shadowmap.cpp,
	  render/subdivision2.cpp, render/texturemap.cpp: Port various bug
	  fixes from the development trunk.  #1113859 ScreenWindow problem.
	  textureinfo() sl command returns 0 for invalid file.  #1037554
	  ensure a trailing '\' is used in searchpaths for Win95.  #1102598
	  catch invalid basis names in RIB.  Fix handling of AOV
	  quantisation.  #1220286 fix handling of facevarying primitive
	  variables on SDS.  Fix texture output memory leaks and duplicate
	  tags.  Support 'vector' variants of cellnoise() sl functions.
	  Fix initialisation of dv in light shaders.

2005-04-16 20:47  pgregory

	* render/ri.cpp: Fix bug #1184401, if a RIB file explicitly
	  redeclared "P", i.e. "vertex point P" it caused a comparison to
	  fail when collecting primitive variable data, the comparison was
	  being done agains the token, not the parsed variable name.

2005-04-03 00:57  pgregory

	* render/ri.cpp: Fix bug #1175571 The RiPointsGeneralPolygonsV
	  routine wasn't dealing with integer primitive variables at all.

2005-02-22 23:43  pgregory

	* render/: imagebuffer.cpp, micropolygon.cpp, micropolygon.h,
	  points.cpp, points.h, quadrics.cpp: Fix bug #1144077. The
	  implementation of motion blurred/DoF micropolygons using the
	  CqDetachedMicropolygon class didn't allow for the special case
	  micropolygon used for Points. The use of CqDetachedMicropolygon
	  has now been removed, and an alternative solution found.

2005-01-26 23:21  pgregory

	* render/ri.cpp: Fix a problem with array primitive variables on
	  RiPointsGeneralPolygons.  We triangulate the general polys and
	  produce a RiPointsPolygons, during which process we need to add
	  to any uniform and facevarying arrays to account for triangles
	  added during triangulation. We weren't taking into account the
	  lenght of each element in an array variable.

2005-01-25 23:27  pgregory

	* render/micropolygon.cpp: Minor optimisation if dPdu or dPdv are
	  not needed.

2005-01-25 23:20  pgregory

	* render/micropolygon.cpp: Fix bug #1104545, Surface derivatives
	  are 0 (on quadrics)

2005-01-24 20:13  pgregory

	* libslparse/parser.yxx: Fix bug #1108592, array variables could
	  not be passed as arguments to functions.

2005-01-17 16:55  pgregory

	* Makefile.am: Add aqsis.spec to the package

2005-01-17 16:21  pgregory

	* ChangeLog: Update changelog ready for release.

2005-01-17 16:10  pgregory

	* aqsis.spec: Update from Tobias

2005-01-14 13:26  pgregory

	* configure.ac, render/version.h: Update version no. to 1.0.0 in
	  preparation for 1.0 launch.

2005-01-10 20:40  cgtobix

	* render/ri.cpp: Removed double SHINYMETAL entry.

2005-01-06 14:09  pgregory

	* render/points.cpp: Fix handling of "Os" on RiPoints.

